The ANCHORIA. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. February 4, 1903.) No. 80. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. H. D. Marshall, for appellant. W. H. Smith, for appellee.

Before WALLACE, LACOMBE, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed, with interest and costs, upon the opinion below. 113 Fed. 982.
